        "Link": "https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/whipped-gorgonzola",
        "Summary": "Choose a mild and creamy Gorgonzola for this dip.",
        "Ingredients": "['4 ounces Gorgonzola Dolce', '4 ounces cream cheese', '¾ cup heavy cream', 'Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper', 'Crudités (such as sliced fennel, sliced baby beets, radishes with tops, cucumbers, and small carrots with tops) and toast points (for serving)']",
        "Instructions": "['Pulse Gorgonzola, cream cheese, and cream in a food processor until smooth; season with salt and pepper. Serve with crudités and toast points alongside.', 'Do Ahead: Dip can be made 5 days ahead. Cover and chill; let sit at room temperature 20 minutes before serving.']",
