        "Summary": "\n\t\tStreet Corn Pasta Salad with a flavorful, super addicting cilantro pesto, avocado and creamy goat cheese. This recipe is not only delicious but it’s a great way to use up your summer corn. The best pasta salad I’ve ever made!\t",
        "Ingredients": "[' For the corn ', ' 2 large ears of corn, shucked and cleaned ', ' 1-2 teaspoons avocado or olive oil ', ' ½ teaspoon chili powder ', ' ½ teaspoon cumin ', ' Freshly ground salt and pepper ', ' For the pasta ', ' 8 ounces bow tie pasta (or your favorite pasta) ', ' 1 red bell pepper, diced ', ' 1/2 avocado, diced ', ' 1/3 cup goat cheese crumbles ', ' ½ cup diced red onion ', ' For the cilantro pesto ', ' 1 cup cilantro leaves (about ½ a bunch) ', ' 1/3 cup roasted or raw cashews ', ' 1 small lime, juiced ', ' 1 clove garlic ', ' 1 jalapeño, seeded ', ' 2 tablespoons olive oil or avocado oil ', ' ¼ teaspoon salt, plus more to taste ', ' Freshly ground black pepper ', ' 1-2 tablespoons water, if necessary to thin the pesto ', ' To garnish:  ', ' Extra cilantro ', ' 1/2 avocado, if desired ', ' 2 tablespoons goat cheese crumbles ']",
